reviews.review_text:
Good Show good sound. This is a good version of this show.I am prefer the aud tapes only because I like the backround sound of us in the crowd.
Bobby was going off on this tour add libbing. Liften to the Stranger.... he goes onn about not the lone ranger. Then during estimated he come up with easy now. Starting in Ventura with his playin raps or scats as some like to call them. Then again at the rocks then the zoo in oak.
Bringing back a favorite Stagger Lee is back!  One of my favorite story tunes.  I was sad to see it go and am glad they brought it back at least for this show.

Ain't no Lone Ranger~! High in treble and Phil is very low in the mix..but still worth a listen..Nice 1st set with a fun Stranger and a sweet Row Jimmy..The 2nd is solid with Never Trust a Women as a opener which I like placed later in the set..Give me something to get the blood pumping as an opener and a song like that to catch my breath and wipe the sweat..3.5 for this show~Forever Grateful>Forever Dead
